\section{Richer Contexts}
\def\doll{\$}
It seems to go cleanly if I allow a lot of stuff in $\Gamma$. The pseudo-hypothesis
$h$, with no variable name, tracks the single bit of information by its presence or absence
 of whether we have morally added a hyp of type $H$ yet. We
let the type $H$ internalize that. The presence of $h$ in the context isn't in any particular place.
Multiple copies of $h$ in the context automatically coalesce. I'm going to punt on deciding
exactly how $\emptyset$ works, but it's meant to be like a collapsed context with a $0$ hyp in it.

We don't have any variable constructors like $x[h]$ anymore.
