\subsection{Weakening}
We let there be a poset on hypotheses and contexts generated by the following:

\begin{itemize}
\item $x :: A \le x : A \le x \div A$
\item $\Gamma, h \le \Gamma$
\item $(x \div A, h) \le (x : A, h)$
\item If $\Gamma \le \Gamma'$ and $\Delta \le \Delta'$ then $\Gamma,\Delta \le \Gamma',\Delta'$.
\end{itemize}

The general weakening theorem is:
\begin{lemma}
If $\Delta \le \Gamma$ and $\Gamma \prov J$, then $\Delta \prov J$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}

\cqed
\end{proof}

